title: Air Fryer Crispy Fish Tacos with Slaw

Ingredients.13: 1 pound cod fillets, cut into bite-sized pieces

Directions.1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Spray the basket of the air fryer with cooking spray.

Directions.2: Combine cabbage slaw, jalapeno pepper, lime juice, olive oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper in a large bowl. Mix until evenly combined and set aside.

Directions.3: Mix together flour, cornmeal, and taco seasoning in a separate bowl. Add fish pieces and toss until evenly coated, discarding any remaining seasoning mix. Place in the prepared air fryer basket and mist lightly with cooking spray.

Directions.4: Cook fish in the preheated air fryer for 5 minutes. Shake the basket, and cook until fish is crispy and flakes easily with a fork, about 5 minutes more. Remove to a paper towel-lined plate.

Directions.5: Place cabbage slaw mixture into the air fryer basket.

Directions.6: Cook until cabbage is caramelized, about 8 minutes, stirring halfway through the cooking time.

Directions.7: Spoon cabbage onto tortillas and top with fish.
